# Portal architecture — FROZEN

Do not redesign, split, or expand the customer portal architecture unless the user explicitly unfreezes it.

## Boundaries

- **waamto-website** = portal UI + BFF (`/api/portal/*`) only.
- **License Engine (wle-api)** = source of truth for licenses, billing, invoices, notifications, identity, org/users.
- **WAAMTO app** = product support / tickets. Portal must NOT own a support-ticket system.
- Do not add a second backend, new DB, or portal-only domain models for commercial data.

## Frozen nav & surfaces

Allowed portal sections (see `portal-nav.ts`):

Dashboard · Licenses · Subscriptions · Invoices · Billing · Organizations · Users · Modules · Business Profile · Notifications · Settings

Plus flows: Plans / Checkout (renew & upgrade). `/portal/support` stays a redirect away from tickets — do not reintroduce portal support UI.

## Patterns to keep

- Aggregate reads via `lib/portal/dashboard.ts` + `/api/portal/dashboard`.
- Mutations go through existing `/api/portal/*` proxies to Engine/commercial clients — no direct browser→Engine secrets.
- Renew / upgrade: `resolvePreferredGateway` + billing renew / plan-change → checkout.
- Invoices: preview always; PDF/download only when Engine marks paid; unpaid watermark on preview.
- Notifications: Engine-backed list + mark-read (include license-expiry alerts).
- Settings: profile + password via identity APIs; no portal-local auth store.

## Explicitly out of scope (until unfrozen)

- Portal support tickets / live chat product
- Portal-side user invite/edit/remove (beyond Engine-fed read views)
- Editable org/business profile writers (beyond what identity already exposes)
- New payment gateway orchestration layers
- Duplicating ERP/app features inside the portal

## Change policy

Bugfixes and Engine-contract wiring inside this shape are OK. New sections, new data stores, or “portal v2” layouts require an explicit user request to unfreeze.
